## Description {#details}

Line entries are used to encode the line tables in <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/gsym/functioninfo">FunctionInfo</a> objects.

They are stored as a sorted vector of these objects and store the address, file and line of the line table row for a given address. The size of a line table entry is calculated by looking at the next entry in the <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/gsym/functioninfo">FunctionInfo</a>&#39;s vector of entries.
